items.title: People as Intelligence vs. People as Biology. Thoughts?
items.summary: I have been thinking about this new research direction for AI all year. I believe it is an error to even call the field AI rather than just simply intelligence or machine intelligence, as the framing largely influences how people approach this. We have literally been transferring different aspects of human intelligence to the machines and we are probably very close to being able to transfer everything now. Then we could build entities that simultaneously capture the best parts of humanity while doing away with the saddest ones. What about intelligent, ethical and 'almost' immortal machines that can survive anywhere? Comments URL: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=46042758 Points: 1 # Comments: 1
